task.summary: Removed a ton of old, unused code. Added version info to online help.
Markdown converter so online documentation in the CLI can be turned into markdown in CILogon's github documentation.
Fixed JeffSpeak in some documentation. It can now be reliably read by most mid-sized primates.
CIL-1069, send mail messages in a background thread.
CIL-1677 Redux, updates to CLI(formatting and such)
Made CLI not care about escaping ids in certain contexts.
Updating build for making the website, plus general build cleanup.
Test of scripts that build everything.
Test of scripts that build everything.
Test of scripts that build everything.

https://github.com/ncsa/security-lib/issues/16 -- state object need to be passed to AbstractServlet so logging of success/failures works.
https://github.com/ncsa/security-lib/issues/17 -- Setting of log and debug level made to conform to expectations in other logging frameworks.
More improvements to logging. Making everything more configurable.
unused client machinery moved to OA4MP. No need for it here.
Checkin before travel. Error if null node rather than an NPE.
Tweak several small things for CLI. In particular, finding objects is now streamlined and object creation is too.
Had a blindingly good idea for printing the online help. https://jira.ncsa.illinois.edu/browse/CIL-1815
Slightly improved object creation in the CLI.
Wrong reference to crypt 8 library. Moved static utility to a class.
https://github.com/ncsa/security-lib/issues/23 corrupt database causing SQL connection leak.

Changges to constructors and initialization of logging. In cases where loggers are used by other components with existing logging (e.g. being used as part of QDL), the same logger should be used everywhere. Allow for it to be injected at instantiation.
Allow for a command to clear a store of all entries in the CLI. This is not needed often, but when it is (e.g. after database corruption) it is essential.

MESSAGE.value: Added java serializationfor a few classes. QDL still officially at least allows it, so need it for that.
Added utility to get all HTTP header parameters properly parsed.
https://github.com/ncsa/security-lib/issues/46 Promoted result sets to first order objects. This makes a lot of batch processing vastly easier.
Mostly formatting updates in the CLI to support result set printing.
https://github.com/ncsa/security-lib/issues/50 wide ranging audit of all help and access for stored objects. This uses the new machinery now consistently.
Saw clarification for help comment. Added it.
Fixed NPE I found in an edge case for formatting output
Batch file processign with indices. This should be kept, but probably best replaced by hijacking System.in
